# claude-transcripts vault excludes (explore-76oc Phase 3, §4.3 — sandbox-validated).
# Whitelist the VARIABLE-DEPTH transcript corpus over the shared ~/.claude/projects
# work-tree, leaving memory (the other vault) and everything else untracked.
#
# The idiom differs from memory.excludes: transcripts live at variable depth
# (main *.jsonl at depth 1, subagents at depth 3+, tool-results/*.txt at depth 2),
# so this uses the UNANCHORED `*` catch-all (NOT `/*`) — the load-bearing fix a
# Phase-3 design review caught (an anchored `/*` re-stages the whole tree incl.
# memory .md). Do NOT edit without re-running the sandbox whitelist assertion
# (bootstrap + selftest: "only transcript paths staged, none under */memory/").
#
# ignore EVERYTHING at every depth
*
# but let git descend into every directory so deep files stay reachable
!*/
# re-include session transcripts at ANY depth (main depth-1 + subagents depth-3+)
!**/*.jsonl
# re-include raw tool outputs (only directly inside a tool-results/ dir)
!**/tool-results/*.txt
# HARD seal on the OTHER vault's tier: prune memory/ last so NOTHING under it is
# re-includable — not even a stray memory/x.jsonl (the cross-vault double-claim fix).
**/memory/
